TITLE: Missing lawyer Ciera Breland's mom believes she was killed
SUMMARY: The mother of Ciera Breland, a lawyer and mother from Indiana who disappeared in February 2022, says her family believes she was killed and hopes her body will be found.

TITLE: SUV smashes into Houston coffee shop, hits two men during live podcast: video
SUMMARY: Two men in Texas were minding their own business, creating content at a coffee shop when an SUV came barreling right at them. The two walked away with minor injuries.

TITLE: NYPD video shows wanted suspects caught on camera defacing more than a century-old Christopher Columbus statue
SUMMARY: The NYPD released video showing two suspects accused of tagging "Murderer" and "Give Us Our Land Back" on a statue of Christopher Columbus commissioned in 1892 in Central Park.

TITLE: Norfolk Southern train collides with dump truck in Cleveland, Ohio, killing at least 1: reports
SUMMARY: A Norfolk Southern employee was reportedly killed Tuesday morning when a train crashed into a dump truck while passing through a Cleveland-Cliffs Cleveland Works property.

TITLE: Southern California residents frustrated after record snowfall traps them for over a week: 'Exhausting'
SUMMARY: While southern California officials are working to clear roads and provide food and emergency services after record snowfall, some residents are frustrated with the response.

TITLE: Human bone found at Milwaukee beach
SUMMARY: A human bone was discovered at Milwaukee beach, Wisconsin, by a person walking along the shore. Other remains were found too but may belong to an animal.

TITLE: California trans child molester's dad denies murder allegations, defends jailhouse calls
SUMMARY: Hannah Tubbs' father says the convicted trans child molester did not kill a man three weeks before a murder trial is set to begin in Kern County, California.

TITLE: Wet weather will hit the West again as the South remains warm
SUMMARY: Several storms systems are forecast to bring more coastal rain and heavy mountain snow to the West as the South is expected to see record high temperatures.

TITLE: Portland's Crime Crisis: Soros-backed DA creating lawless, 'free-for-all' mentality, trial attorney says
SUMMARY: Some Portland residents say lack of prosecution is contributing to the city's crime crisis. Here's how Portland's prosecution rates compare to neighboring counties.

TITLE: Soros DA put murder case on 'back burner' because it doesn't 'fit' liberal agenda: victim's family
SUMMARY: The brother of a man killed in Austin, Texas, is slamming the city's Soros-funded district attorney for his handling of the case that he says has been put on the "back burner."

TITLE: University of Houston scraps diversity, equity and inclusion statements from hiring practices
SUMMARY: The University of Houston system announced it will ditch diversity, equity and inclusion statements from hiring practices after a directive from the governor's office.

TITLE: US Border Patrol transfers agents to Canadian border amid migrant crisis
SUMMARY: Extra border patrol agents have been transferred to points of the U.S.-Canada border as an influx of migrants are starting to cross into the country from the north.

TITLE: Los Angeles County jury awards $1.5M to prosecutor suing DA George Gascon for retaliation
SUMMARY: A Los Angeles County jury awarded a prosecutor $1.5 million as part of a retaliation lawsuit against District Attorney George Gascon and his office.

TITLE: Arizona rancher charged with killing illegal migrant pleads not guilty during Monday arraignment
SUMMARY: An Arizona rancher pleaded not guilty to murdering a Mexican migrant on his ranch on Jan. 30, maintaining he fired warning shots into the sky and not at a group of armed migrants.

TITLE: Catholic Charities of Omaha employee sues over active shooter drill
SUMMARY: Catholic Charities of Omaha employee Sandra Lopez is suing the organization for alleged failure to notify her that an active shooter drill was staged and no real danger was present.

TITLE: Atlanta 'Cop City' protest quickly turns violent and fiery, video shows
SUMMARY: Atlanta Police posted video showing rioters storm the future site of a public safety and training center, before throwing rocks and fireworks, and setting equipment on fire.

TITLE: Car pulled from Arkansas lake contained body of person missing since 2008
SUMMARY: Police in Arkansas discovered a submerged vehicle in Lake Hamilton containing the body of an individual linked to a February 2008 missing persons report.

TITLE: Sunday funeral planned for fallen Indiana state trooper
SUMMARY: The funeral of Indiana State Police Master Trooper James Bailey, who was struck by a fleeing suspect's vehicle, has been planned for Sunday.

TITLE: Florida woman pleads guilty in million-dollar COVID relief scam
SUMMARY: Danielle Miller, 32, of Miami, pleaded guilty to wire fraud and aggravated identity theft following a federal indictment for fraudulently receiving over $1 million in COVID relief.

TITLE: Father of Nashville Waffle House shooter sentenced to 18 months
SUMMARY: The father of the Nashville Waffle House shooter was sentenced to 18 months for illegally giving his son an assault-style rifle he used to fatally shoot four people.

TITLE: Maryland police fatally shoot man with knife
SUMMARY: Maryland police fatally shot a man who was coming at them with a knife after ignoring multiple commands to stop. The now deceased man was hiding in a closet.

TITLE: Former California TV doctor sentenced for asking child for naked pictures
SUMMARY: A former California TV doctor has been sentenced after pleading no contest to asking a child for naked pictures. The man was arrested in 2019 after asking a 9-year-old for nude pictures.

TITLE: Arizona teen found dead, wrapped in blanket; parents arrested
SUMMARY: An Arizona man and woman have been charged with concealing a body that is possibly their teenage son who they said had died.

TITLE: Conservative group wins legal victory in case over teachers union's $12.5M COVID loan
SUMMARY: The Mackinac Center for Public Policy will claim a $22,500 reward for blowing the whistle on $12.5 million in COVID relief funds received by an ineligible teachers union.
